## Component Organization Patterns

### Shared vs Variants Structure (REQUIRED FOR MOST COMPONENTS)
- **Use "shared" section for common properties**: Properties that are the same across all color variants (border radius, padding, height, focus ring dimensions, min-width)
- **Use "variants" section for color-specific properties**: Background, border, text, and icon colors that change per variant
- **Variants structure**: `variants.{color-name}.{style-type}.{property}.{state}`
  - Examples: `variants.primary.outline.background.hover`, `variants.error.default.text.active`

### Nested Component Elements
- **Typography section**: Place shared typography outside variants since font size/weight is usually consistent across colors
- **Icon sizes section**: Place icon sizes outside variants since size is consistent across colors
- **Icon colors**: Embed within each variant since colors change per variant
- **Specialized content**: Group related functionality (addon, prefix, suffix, dropdown, etc.)

### Size-Dependent Properties (CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS)
- **Component height**: Include height tokens for each size variant in shared section
- **Min-width requirement**: All components must include min-width property in shared section
- **Size-responsive properties**: Properties that change based on component size (padding, typography, icons)
- **Consistent scaling**: All size-dependent properties should scale appropriately together

### Multi-Style Support
- **Style variants within color variants**: Support multiple styles (outline, filled, ghost) within each color
- **Consistent state structure**: All styles should support the same states (default, hover, active, focused, disabled)
- **Focus ring integration**: Include focus ring colors and shadows within each variant for proper visual hierarchy

### Color Variant Patterns (STANDARDIZED)
- **Standard color variants**: `primary`, `neutral`, `success`, `error`, `warning`
- **Style types**: `outline`, `filled`, `ghost`, `default` (component-specific)
- **Property structure within variants**:
  ```json
  "variants": {
    "{color}": {
      "{style}": {
        "background": { /* all states */ },
        "border": { /* all states */ },
        "text": { /* all states including placeholder */ },
        "icon": { /* all states */ },
        "focus": {
          "ring": { "value": "{color.border.{color}.subtle.2}", "type": "color" },
          "shadow": { "value": "/* specific shadow for variant */", "type": "boxShadow" }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```

## Icon Token Guidelines (UPDATED)
- **Icon colors**: Embed within color variants (not shared section) since colors change per variant
- **Icon sizes**: Define separately in dedicated icon section (consistent across color variants)
- **Icon states**: Include all interaction states (default, hover, active, focused, disabled) for icon colors
- **Multiple icon types**: For components with leading/trailing/help icons, organize by position and size
- **Do NOT duplicate icon properties**: If icon color changes by variant, put in variants; if size changes by component size, put in dedicated section

## Typography Organization (STANDARDIZED)

### Simple Typography Pattern
**For components with consistent typography across variants**:
```json
"text": {
  "typography": {
    "xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.xs}", "type": "string"},
    "sm": {"value": "{font.body.regular.sm}", "type": "string"},
    "md": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "string"},
    "lg": {"value": "{font.body.regular.base}", "type": "string"}
  }
}
```

### Complex Typography Pattern
**For components with multiple typography contexts**:
```json
"text": {
  "typography": {
    "title": {
      "xs": {"value": "{font.body.semibold.xs}", "type": "string"},
      "sm": {"value": "{font.body.semibold.sm}", "type": "string"},
      "md": {"value": "{font.body.semibold.md}", "type": "string"},
      "lg": {"value": "{font.body.semibold.base}", "type": "string"}
    },
    "body": {
      "xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.xs}", "type": "string"},
      "sm": {"value": "{font.body.regular.sm}", "type": "string"},
      "md": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "string"},
      "lg": {"value": "{font.body.regular.base}", "type": "string"}
    },
    "caption": {
      "xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.2xs}", "type": "string"},
      "sm": {"value": "{font.body.regular.xs}", "type": "string"},
      "md": {"value": "{font.body.regular.sm}", "type": "string"},
      "lg": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "string"}
    }
  }
}
```

## Component Selection Guidelines

### When to Use Shared/Variants Pattern
- **Interactive components** with multiple color states (buttons, inputs, tags)
- **Form elements** requiring consistent structure across variants
- **Components with hover/focus/active states**
- **Multi-style components** (outline, filled, ghost)

### When to Use Container Pattern  
- **Simple utility components** with minimal color variation
- **Binary state components** (checkbox, radio, toggle)
- **Components where structure varies significantly** between variants
- **Single-purpose components** without complex interactions

### When to Use Simplified Variants Pattern
- **Informational components** (alerts, badges, toasts)
- **Display components** without complex interaction states
- **Components with simple color theming** only
- **Read-only components** (avatars, indicators)

## Critical Rules for All Component Token Generation

1. **STRUCTURE CLEANUP:**
   - Remove all schema/metadata: $schema, $description, name, version, description
   - Use actual component name as root key (e.g., "input", "button") not "component"
   - Remove documentation sections: responsive, states, variants, types
   - Keep only core token definitions: size, color, border-radius, container

2. **SIZE NAMING STANDARDIZATION (CRITICAL):**
   - **Use standard scale**: xs, sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl
   - **Avoid legacy naming**: 3xs, 2xs should be migrated to standard scale
   - **Consistent sizing**: All size-dependent properties use same scale within component

3. **TOKEN HIERARCHY WORKFLOW:**
   - Check primitive tokens first - if value doesn't exist, add to primitive tokens
   - Add to semantic tokens - create semantic reference to primitive
   - Reference in component tokens - use semantic token reference
   - Never create arbitrary values - all values must flow through primitive → semantic → component

4. **STATE NAMING CONSISTENCY (CRITICAL):**
   - **Standard states**: default, hover, active, focused, disabled
   - **Component-specific states**: checked/unchecked, open/closed, filled, placeholder
   - **All color properties must have identical state structure**
   - **Include placeholder state for all text properties in form components**

5. **STRUCTURAL PATTERN SELECTION:**
   - **Shared/Variants**: For interactive components with consistent structure
   - **Container**: For simple components with minimal variation
   - **Simplified Variants**: For informational components

6. **REQUIRED ELEMENTS:**
   - **Min-width**: All components must include min-width property in shared/container section
   - **Form labels**: All form components must include label section
   - **Helper text**: All form components must include helper-text section
   - **Focus states**: Interactive components must include focus ring and shadow

7. **ORGANIZATION ORDER:**
   - shared/container → text → icon → label → helper-text → variants → specialized sections

8. **SEMANTIC TOKEN REFERENCES:**
   - Use direct semantic tokens without "tokens." prefix
   - Prioritize semantic tokens over primitive when available
   - Format fractional values as 0[5] not 0.5

9. **TRANSPARENT VALUES:**
   - **NEVER use raw "transparent"** - always use semantic token reference
   - Background: `{color.background.transparent}`
   - Border: `{color.border.transparent}`

10. **ICON ORGANIZATION:**
    - **Icon colors**: Within color variants (changes per variant)
    - **Icon sizes**: Separate dedicated section (consistent across variants)
    - **Multiple positions**: Organize by position (leading, trailing, help)

11. **HEIGHT TOKEN HANDLING:**
    - **Preferred**: Use semantic height tokens `{size.height.xs}`
    - **Fallback**: Use direct size tokens `{size.20}` when semantic unavailable
    - **Size scaling**: Height should scale appropriately with component size

12. **SPECIALIZED SECTIONS:**
    - **Place after variants**: addon, prefix, suffix, dropdown, etc.
    - **Context-specific**: Create tokens for specialized functionality
    - **Maintain consistency**: Use same color and spacing patterns as main component

13. **FIGMA OPTIMIZATION:**
    - Clean JSON structure without metadata
    - Direct token mapping from Figma component properties
    - Reference existing primitive/semantic tokens properly 